	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-08-19T05:08:15">F&amp;C Global Smaller Companies PLC is a United Kingdom-based investment trust company. The Company's investment objective is to invest in smaller companies across the world in order to secure a high total return. The Company pursues its investment objective by investing in stocks in a range of industry sectors and geographic locations. The Company invests mainly in quoted equities, including those quoted on the Alternative Investment Market. It invests in other types of securities or assets, including collective funds. F&amp;C Investment Business Limited (FCIB) is the investment manager of the Company.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-01-11T20:42:46">BRIEF: For the six months ended 31 October 2015, F&amp;C Global Smaller Companies PLC revenues decreased from L23.5M to -L5.7M. Net loss totaled L9.5M vs. income of L20.2M. Revenues reflect Gains on Investments decrease from L19.8M to -L9.7M, Foreign exchange gains/ (losses) decrease of 76% to L64K. Dividend per share remained flat at L0.03. Basic Earnings per Share excluding Extraordinary Items decreased from L0.39 to -L0.18.</Text>
